'''Georg von Wyß''' (or '''Wyss''') (March 31, 1816 &ndash; December 17, 1893) was a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] historian. He was born and died in [[Zürich]].<ref>[[Bavarian Academy of Sciences and Humanities]]. ''[[Allgemeine Deutsche Biographie]]'', volume 44. 1898.</ref>
From 1870, he served as a "full professor" at the [[University of Zurich]], being appointed [[rector (academia)|rector]] in 1872.<ref>[http://www.histvv.uzh.ch/dozenten/wyss_g.html University of Zurich » University Archives] Historische Vorlesungsverzeichnisse</ref> He was a founding member of the ''Allgemeine Geschichtforschenden Gesellschaft'' (1841), holding the office of president from 1854 to 1893.
Among his literary works is ''Geschichte der Historiographie in der Schweiz'' (History of [[historiography]] in Switzerland, 1895). Other significant writings by Wyss are: * ''Biographie von Nicolo Paganini'', 1846 &ndash; Biography of [[Nicolo Paganini]]. * ''Zürich am Ausgange des dreizehnten Jahrhunderts'', 1876 &ndash; Zürich at the close of the thirteenth century.<ref>[https://openlibrary.org/authors/OL2370488A/Georg_von_Wyss Open Library] (publications)</ref>
