'''Iglunga''' (previously: '''Iglungayut''') was an [[Inuit]] settlement, now uninhabited, in [[Qikiqtaaluk Region]], [[Nunavut]], Canada.

==Information==
It is located on a [[Baffin Island]] offshore island at the southern entrance into Bon Accord Harbour,<ref name="Arcticpilot">{{cite book|last=Dodd|first=G. J. |author2=G. P. Benson |author3=D. T. Watts |others=Great Britain. Hydrographic Dept|title=Arctic pilot|publisher=Hydrographer of the Navy|year=1976|edition=Digitized Apr 3, 2009|volume=3|pages=289|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mYsNAQAAIAAJ&q=Iglunga&dq=Iglunga&client=firefox-a}}</ref> southwest of [[Auyuittuq National Park Reserve]]. The nearest community is [[Pangnirtung, Nunavut|Pangnirtung]]. The elevation is {{convert|3|ft|m|abbr=on}}. The name change from Iglungayut to Iglunga occurred 4 July 1957.<ref name="Arcticinstitute">{{cite book|title=Arctic|publisher=Arctic Institute of North America|year=1958|edition=Digitized Dec 20, 2006|volume=11|pages=129|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2UcYAAAAIAAJ&q=Iglungayut&dq=Iglungayut&client=firefox-a}}</ref>

